---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const topics = [
  {
    icon: '🧠',
    title: 'Reasoning Models Changed Everything',
    tag: 'Models',
    tagColor: '#d4a574',
    points: [
      'o3, o4-mini, and Gemini Deep Think use chain-of-thought reasoning — they think before answering, dramatically improving code accuracy.',
      'Claude Opus 4.7 introduced "xhigh" effort — more thinking tokens = better results on hard problems, but higher cost.',
      'GPT-5.4 is the first general-purpose model with native computer-use — it can operate browsers and desktops via screenshots + mouse/keyboard.',
      'Reasoning models are trained via reinforcement learning on tool use. They decide when to search, code, or browse — not just respond.',
    ],
  },
  {
    icon: '🔌',
    title: 'MCP Is the New Standard for Tool Integration',
    tag: 'Protocol',
    tagColor: '#10a37f',
    points: [
      'Model Context Protocol (MCP) lets any AI model connect to any tool via a standardized JSON-RPC interface. Think USB-C for AI.',
      'Every major vendor now supports MCP: VS Code, Claude, Cursor, Windsurf, JetBrains. Build once, run everywhere.',
      'MCP servers expose tools, resources, and prompts. Clients discover them at runtime — no hardcoding tool lists.',
      'GPT-5.4\'s "tool search" reduces tokens by 47% with MCP. Instead of loading all tool definitions upfront, the model searches for them on demand.',
    ],
  },
  {
    icon: '🤖',
    title: 'Agentic Coding Is Production-Ready',
    tag: 'Agents',
    tagColor: '#6366f1',
    points: [
      'GitHub Copilot now runs as an agent: it reads files, runs terminal commands, iterates on errors, and commits fixes — not just autocomplete.',
      'Claude Code, Codex CLI, and Cursor Composer all support autonomous multi-step workflows with file editing and testing.',
      'Agent mode works best with clear instructions files (.github/copilot-instructions.md) that define project conventions.',
      'The key pattern: define the task → agent plans → executes → verifies → iterates. Human reviews the PR, not every keystroke.',
    ],
  },
  {
    icon: '📐',
    title: 'Context Windows Are 10× Bigger — Use Them',
    tag: 'Architecture',
    tagColor: '#4285f4',
    points: [
      'Llama 4 Scout supports 10M tokens. GPT-5.4 and Gemini 3.x support 1M+. That\'s entire codebases in a single prompt.',
      'RAG is still important for cost/latency, but "stuff the context" is now viable for many production use cases.',
      'Long context doesn\'t mean infinite attention. Models still lose accuracy in the middle of very long inputs (the "lost in the middle" problem).',
      'Practical tip: put the most important context at the beginning and end of your prompt, not buried in the middle.',
    ],
  },
  {
    icon: '🏗️',
    title: 'The IDE Is Becoming an Agent Runtime',
    tag: 'Tools',
    tagColor: '#007acc',
    points: [
      'VS Code agent mode lets Copilot edit files, run commands, manage git — turning your IDE into an autonomous development environment.',
      'Custom instructions (.instructions.md, .prompt.md) let you persist project context so every chat session knows your stack.',
      'BYOK (Bring Your Own Key) lets you use Claude, Gemini, or other models directly in VS Code — you\'re not locked to one provider.',
      'Google launched "Antigravity" — a full agent-first IDE. JetBrains has Junie. The IDE war is now an agent war.',
    ],
  },
  {
    icon: '🔐',
    title: 'AI Security Is a Real Attack Surface',
    tag: 'Security',
    tagColor: '#ef4444',
    points: [
      'Prompt injection is the #1 risk: untrusted data in prompts can hijack model behavior. Always sanitize inputs at system boundaries.',
      'Supply chain attacks now include poisoned training data and malicious MCP servers. Vet your tool integrations.',
      'Claude Opus 4.7 and GPT-5.4 both deploy "cyber safeguards" — automated monitoring that blocks prohibited security requests.',
      'OpenAI\'s Privacy Filter (Apr 2026) and Anthropic\'s Cyber Verification Program signal that vendors are treating this seriously.',
    ],
  },
  {
    icon: '💰',
    title: 'Pricing & Cost Optimization Matter More Than Ever',
    tag: 'Business',
    tagColor: '#ff9d00',
    points: [
      'GPT-5.4: $2.50/$15/M tokens. Claude Opus 4.7: $5/$25/M. Cached input is 10× cheaper — design for cache hits.',
      'Reasoning effort levels (low/medium/high/xhigh) let you trade accuracy for cost. Most tasks don\'t need max effort.',
      'Open-weight models (DeepSeek-R1, Qwen3, Llama 4) offer zero API cost for self-hosted inference. MIT/Apache licensing.',
      'Batch and flex pricing from OpenAI is 50% off. If your workload isn\'t real-time, use async processing.',
    ],
  },
  {
    icon: '🌐',
    title: 'Open-Source Is Closing the Gap Fast',
    tag: 'Ecosystem',
    tagColor: '#238636',
    points: [
      'DeepSeek-R1 (MIT license) matches o1 on reasoning benchmarks. Qwen3 tops open-source leaderboards with Apache 2.0.',
      'Llama 4 Maverick beats GPT-4o on many benchmarks while being open-weight with 17B active params.',
      'MoE architecture is the open-source secret weapon: 400B total params but only 17B active = efficient inference.',
      'Hugging Face, Ollama, and vLLM make running frontier-class models on your own hardware increasingly practical.',
    ],
  },
];
---
<BaseLayout title="What Devs Should Know" activeNav="knowledge">

<main class="container">
  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2>💡 What Developers Should Know</h2>
      <p>Essential knowledge about AI models, tools, and practices — updated with verified facts from official sources</p>
    </div>

    <div class="knowledge-grid">
      {topics.map((topic, i) => (
        <article class="knowledge-card" style={`--card-accent:${topic.tagColor};animation-delay:${i * 60}ms;`}>
          <div class="knowledge-header">
            <span class="knowledge-icon">{topic.icon}</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="knowledge-title">{topic.title}</h3>
              <span class="tag" style={`background:${topic.tagColor}22;color:${topic.tagColor};border:1px solid ${topic.tagColor}44;`}>{topic.tag}</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <ul class="knowledge-points">
            {topic.points.map(p => <li>{p}</li>)}
          </ul>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top:40px;padding:20px;background:var(--surface);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:var(--radius);">
      <p style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--text-muted);">
        <strong style="color:var(--accent);">ℹ️ Sources:</strong> All facts verified against official announcements from Anthropic, OpenAI, Google DeepMind, Meta AI, and VS Code. Last updated April 2026.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .knowledge-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(420px, 1fr));
    gap: 20px;
    margin-top: 24px;
  }

  .knowledge-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 24px;
    transition: border-color 0.3s, transform 0.2s;
    animation: fadeInUp 0.4s ease-out both;
  }

  .knowledge-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--card-accent);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .knowledge-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 14px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .knowledge-icon {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 2px;
  }

  .knowledge-title {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 0 0 6px;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .knowledge-points {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .knowledge-points li {
    position: relative;
    padding: 8px 0 8px 20px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.55;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .knowledge-points li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .knowledge-points li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--card-accent);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  @keyframes fadeInUp {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(12px); }
    to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .knowledge-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
